{"key":"processedPost-10649950","value":{"id":10649950,"first":10649817,"last":10650030,"when":1247196697,"utime":"07/10/09 06:31 AM","cleanedPost":"I count a quart/liter jar of spawn as 1 quart.&nbsp; Of course it's less than a full quart or liter of actual grain, but it's what fits in the jar and that's what counts.&nbsp; When I make bulk substrates, I always just eyeball the measurements anyway, so it's all good.&nbsp; Don't worry about getting percentages exact.<br />As you go up in the quantities of scale, there's even more fudge room.&nbsp; When I'm mixing bulk substrates, I shovel manure or sawdust, etc., from my wheelbarrow to a cement mixer, spray the hose on it until it looks right, toss in a shovel or two of gypsum and rice bran and call it good after the mixer spins for a minute or so.&nbsp; Nothing gets an exact measure.<br />RR"}}